5: Hey, sorry to keep you waiting.
8:
What're you acting all surprised for?
I said they were alive. Didn't believe
me?
17:
Thank goodness you're alive! I was
hoping against hope that you
survived!
21:
So you're getting by as a dancer in
this world too...
24:
Say, do you still have that hairpin
from way back when?
30:
There's no mistaking it—that's the
symbol of the Dunestrings.
38:
They're one of the peoples that lived
in the borderlands. I only found out
about them after Nina disappeared...
40:
I saw their symbol in a place that
might be her hometown.
44:
...Thanks for bringing me all the way
here, Nimbus.
45:
But... I thought you never wanted to
come back to this world.
48:
Well, this sure ain't my ideal
vacation spot, but...
53:
Hands where I can see them! Or else
you'll get a taste of my electro spear—
56:
You're Dunestring hunters, ain't you?
Relax, we're not with the kingdom.
59:
I'm the Hellcat of the Dunes. I used to
belong to Rolan.
65:
Even if ain't directly related, I got
some business here too.
70:
Nina. Though we do not know you,
you are one of us. We are glad to
welcome you home.
73:
What happened to her family? Are
they still here?
76:
About twenty years ago, raiders
took many of our families.
77:
But we lost even more people in the
fight against the kingdom...
79:
You family was most likely among
their number.
83: You sure you're ready to go?
86:
Yeah... Thanks, Nimbus. I heard
enough.
88:
I'm not really all that shocked.
Besides, my first family will always
be the people I journeyed with
way back when.
89:
I even have a new one now, in the
Endless Blue.
95:
Sorry, Nina. Can I ask you to do
something?
98:
I'm gonna have some guards escort
you back, but then you'll have to
ditch 'em in town and look for a guy
named Haaj.
103:
Consider it part of... the minor
business I gotta take care of.
109:
Haridal told me some people got
their hands on remnants of the
Titan...
111:
Specifically parts that'll let 'em take
control of the kingdom's puppets.
114:
So what if you got like ten of those
things. Do you really think you can
make a difference?
123:
If you truly followed Lord Rolan, why
do you interfere?
127:
He wouldn't have wanted this. Not
more bloodshed after everything.
131:
I'm here to make sure it doesn't
happen.
149:
Come get some, you oversized piles
of trash!
152:
Did you really think we only had ten
of them? We know better than
anyone that we need an army to
take down our foe.
154:
Hellcat of the Dunes. If you don't
back down, we'll just have to get rid
of you first!
162:
*pant* Damn it... Those two are
gonna be pissed at me again...
169: Sorry we took so long to get here!
173:
Idiot... You're beyond late, you know
that?
177: Those punks... Rolan... I had to...
182:
We know! Just... save your breath.
Take it easy. We got this.
186:
Counting on you... You're my best
pal...
190:
...Hey. What happened after I passed
out?
194:
We took care of the golems.
Rakisha's speaking with the
Dunestrings now.
202:
Also, you're gonna have to start your
training over since you messed up
all your progress.
211:
You pretend not to care, but you
always help out in the end.
217:
Putting my big body and strength to
use.
223:
And now you pass out after getting
the last word in? Unfair...
